To send an array of login attempts within the original message you sent, you would modify the JSON object in the fourth element of your original message to be an array of objects that contain the email, password, and code fields for each login attempt, like this:

["auth",42,"login",[
  {"email":"xxx1@xxx","password":"xxxxxxxx","code":"222222"},
  {"email":"xxx2@xxx","password":"yyyyyyyy","code":"333333"}
]]

Now, if you want to add a third login attempt to this message, you can modify the message to include an additional object in the array, like this:

["auth",42,"login",[
  {"email":"xxx1@xxx","password":"xxxxxxxx","code":"222222"},
  {"email":"xxx2@xxx","password":"yyyyyyyy","code":"333333"},
  {"email":"xxx3@xxx","password":"zzzzzzzz","code":"444444"}
]]

In this example, we've added a third object to the array in the fourth element of the message, with a new set of email, password, and code values for a third login attempt. 

By modifying the JSON object in the message to include an array of objects, you can send multiple login attempts within a single message.
